Chukwudi Akasike, Port Harcourt Renowned retired Justice of the Supreme Court, Justice Adolphus Karibi-Whyte, is dead. The 88-year-old Karibi-Whyte died in Port Harcourt, the Rivers State capital. His son, Gogo, who disclosed this to The PUNCH, said his father died about 6 pm on Friday. The late Karibi-Whyte is survived by seven children.